# Supabase — Query Performance & Optimization Reference

> First stop: Supabase Dashboard → Advisors → Performance Advisor.
> It finds missing indexes automatically. Fix those first before manual analysis.

---

## Step 1 — Find Slow Queries

### Supabase Dashboard (easiest)
```
Supabase Dashboard → Reports → Query Performance
Shows: slowest queries by total time, average time, calls
Click any query to see its full text and EXPLAIN plan
```

### pg_stat_statements (SQL — requires extension enabled)
```sql
-- Top 10 slowest queries by total time
SELECT
  SUBSTRING(query, 1, 80) AS query_preview,
  calls,
  ROUND(total_exec_time::NUMERIC, 0) AS total_ms,
  ROUND(mean_exec_time::NUMERIC, 1)  AS avg_ms,
  ROUND((100 * total_exec_time / SUM(total_exec_time) OVER())::NUMERIC, 1) AS pct
FROM pg_stat_statements
WHERE query NOT LIKE '%pg_%'
ORDER BY total_exec_time DESC
LIMIT 10;
```

